*[[Special attack]] weapon (e.g. [[burning claws]] or [[dragon dagger]])
*1 [[divine super combat potion]]
*Many [[Prayer potion]]s or [[Super restore|Super restores]]
** Prayer can also be restored by catching [[moonlight moth]]s outside of Amoxliatl's chamber, albeit more slowly
*[[Manta ray]] or other food ([[monkfish]], [[shark]], etc.)
**All of Amoxliatl's damage is theoretically avoidable, so experienced players may opt to only bring a few food in case of emergency. Players with lower damage may need more food as the fight will last longer and have less available damage-free floor space.
** A cheap but decent-healing food such as [[potato with cheese]] or a high healing and gold-efficient [[hunter meat]] such as [[cooked sunlight antelope]] or [[cooked pyre fox]] are also good alternative foods.
* [[Ectoplasmator]] to receive Prayer experience each kill
*[[Pendant of ates|Pendant of Ates]] for teleporting to the [[Twilight Temple]]
*[[Book of the dead]] for casting resurrection spells on the [[Arceuus spellbook]]
*[[Rune pouch]] and runes for [[Thrall]] spells and [[Death charge]]
*[[Teleport to house (tablet)|House tablets]] (or [[construct. cape]]/[[max cape]]) or [[desert amulet 4]]

